I really don't like having to leave negative reviews, and all the staff I've talked to here have been really nice and understanding, but I have never, never, NEVER gone to this little Ceasers and waited less than 45 minutes. And the 45 is on a good day.  More often than not I end up sitting and waiting for around an hour for one single topping, $5 pizza to the point where I was even asked once "What are you even waiting for?" because they had apparently forgotten I had ordered and given my order to someone who had just walked in, meaning I waited another 30 minutes til they made another one. There was even one memorable occasion where it took over 2 hours to get my food (though the cashiers were really nice about the whole thing and did comp me a soda to apologize).  This has escalated to the point where I've started only putting in pick up orders over the app and -since it's only a 8 minute walk from my house- only leaving when I get the notification saying my order is done so I can at least spend the hour wait (as opposed to the 22 minutes I'm told after putting my order in) in the comfort of my own home instead of sitting on an uncomfortable bench praying my phone doesn't die I've been stuck here so long. Again.  All in all it's not a horrible place. Again, the staff is really nice, the space while could use a good mopping isn't concerning levels of dirty, and I've never had an issue with the food itself. But the consistently horrible wait time just drags the whole experience down, so while I won't say it's the worst Little Ceasers I've been in and never order from here again, I do have to stress to consider the wait before going down there, cause your chances of having an in and out encounter are slim to none.
